    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-04-27T20:50:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-04-27T20:50:00-05:00" n="134"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d134">
                <head>134. Telegram From <gloss type="from">Operation <gloss
                            target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1">PBSUCCESS</gloss> Headquarters in
                        Florida</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Central Intelligence Agency</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d134fn1">Source: Central Intelligence Agency,
                        Job 79–01025A, Box 3, Folder 8. Secret; Routine; RYBAT; <gloss
                            target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1">PBSUCCESS</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>[<hi rend="italic">place not declassified</hi>], <date
                        calendar="gregorian" when="1954-04-28T01:50:00+00:00">April 28, 1954,
                        0150Z</date>.</dateline>
                <p>2179. Re: HGGA 936.<note n="2" xml:id="d134fn2">Not printed. (Ibid., Box 53,
                        Folder 6)</note>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Increasing Catholic activities in <gloss target="#t_WSBURNT1"
                            >WSBURNT</gloss>, noted in ref, make supporting action by Catholic
                        Church dignitaries, lay groups, publications elsewhere in SGRANGER highly
                        desirable for effect in <gloss target="#t_WSBURNT1">WSBURNT</gloss> and
                        internationally.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Suggest that [<hi rend="italic">2 codewords not declassified</hi>]
                        committee in [<hi rend="italic">place not declassified</hi>] and contacts in
                            [<hi rend="italic">3 places not declassified</hi>] and anywhere else in
                        SGRANGER might be contacted through stations concerned on via <gloss
                            target="#t_PBPRIME1">PBPRIME</gloss> Catholic channels.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>Action might be tied to pastoral letter already publicized and could aim
                        at: <list>
                            <label>A.</label>
                            <item>Warning against spread atheistic communism</item>
                            <label>B.</label>
                            <item>Prayer, assistance for endangered faithful in <gloss
                                    target="#t_WSBURNT1">WSBURNT</gloss>, defense of their Catholic
                                schools, youth activities, other church assets</item>
                            <label>C.</label>
                            <item>Faithful to avoid spiritual contamination from Commie-controlled
                                    <gloss target="#t_WSBURNT1">WSBURNT</gloss> government agencies,
                                fronts, propaganda media.</item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_LINC1">LINC</gloss> answering ref by dispatch.</item>
                    <label>5.</label>
                    <item>Advise.</item>
                </list>
            </div>
        </body>
